revision.comment: Initial release
revision.text:
This property [[description::describes a short descripton of a page.]] The type of this property is "[[has type::text]]."
Usually this property is annotated by the [[Help:Semantic templates|semantic template]] <nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[Template:Docinfo|docinfo]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki> automatically. Also the value of this property can be quoted easily by using a template <nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[Template:Documentation desc|documentation desc]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki>. Please see the documentation of these templates for detailed information.
At the moment, all annotations including this property are ingored in some namespace, e.g. Template:, due to a site cofiguration [[Help:Configuration#smwgNamespacesWithSemanticLinks|$smwgNamespacesWithSemanticLinks]]. In order to work around this problem, an alternative method to define tempalte descriptions are prepared by using template <nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[Template:Documentation desctext|documentation desctext]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki>. Please see [[Template:Documentation desctext]] doumentation for more information.

A test property used on some sample pages. The type of this attribute is [[has type::Page]].
You can create a new [[Has default form::Location]] with this property.
== Inverse relationships == The pages for [[Germany]] and [[California]] show various techniques to derive its inverse ''Location of''.
== Transitive relationships == For this wiki we will pretend that located in is transitive, so that things located in a province located in a country are located in that country. The page for [[Germany]] shows various techniques to derive this. (As a counter-example, Turkey is located in both Europe and Asia, but regions within Turkey are only in one or the other.)
[[Category:Sample pages]]

revision.text: This property points to the '''master [[has type::page]]''' of some content page of the document. Master pages are usually the most up-to-date English versions of some content. By pointing to the same master page, different pages can indicate that they cover the same topic but maybe for a different langauge or software version.
This property is specified as [[Has type::Text|text]] and is part of the meta data subobject. ==See also == [[Property:Has subobject]]

revision.text:
'''{{PAGENAME}}''' defines the surface area of a body, such as in astronomy. The type of this attribute is [[has type::Quantity]]. Its units are * [[Corresponds to::1 m²]]
The [[Help:Semantic templates|semantic template]] [[Template:Surface area]] provides a simple way to simultaneously annotate a page with this property and display its value in a standardized scientific notation.
=== Subproperty of === Surface area is a [[Help:Special property Subproperty of|subproperty]] of [[Subproperty of::Area]]. You can query for anything with an Area and pick up pages with this subproperty, but you have to name all subproperties. {{#ask:[[Area::+]] |?Area |?Surface area |limit=5 |headers=show |mainlabel=page with an "area" |link=all |class=sortable wikitable smwtable |order=DESC |sort=Area }}
[[Category:sample pages]]
